               <floruit notBefore="1841" notAfter="1867">He was the 107th metropolitan of the 
                  Ethiopian Orthodox Church who was consecrated by 
                  <persName ref="PRS2965ButrusV">Buṭrus VII</persName> at the age of 
                  21  in <date>1841</date> and  succeeded ʾabuna <persName ref="PRS11137QerellosII">Qerǝllos II</persName> after the church remained without a metropolitan 
                  for nearly 13 years.
                  His first 14 years were characterized by disunity and conflict. 
                  But when  
                  <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Tewodros II</persName>
                  assumed the throne, he enjoyed a short period of relative peace and authority.</floruit>
               <death when="1867"> He died on <date>1867</date>.</death>
            </person>
